    "contenu": "The document outlines the steps for properly opening a bottle of Champagne to maximize enjoyment and safety. Here’s a breakdown of the steps:\n\n### Opening Champagne: A Step-by-Step Guide\n\n1. **Cool the Champagne**: Avoid shaking the bottle, as most prefer not to wear their Champagne. Chilling reduces internal pressure, making the bottles safer and easier to open, but too cold can mute the flavors.\n\n2. **Remove the Foil and Secure the Cork**:\n   - Expose the cork and wire cage.\n   - Hold the bottle neck with your left hand and use your index finger or thumb to press down on the metal cap.\n   - Control the cork to prevent it from popping out at high speed.\n\n3. **Loosen the Cage and Then Switch Hands**:\n   - With your right hand, untwist the wire that holds the cork (about six and a half turns).\n   - Completely loosen the cage but do not remove it.\n   - Transfer the bottle neck to your right hand while still controlling the cork.\n   - Use your right hand to firmly grasp both cage and cork together and shift your left hand to the bottom of the bottle.\n\n4. **Turn the Bottle to Loosen and Ease Out the Cork**:\n   - Rotate the bottle a slow quarter turn to loosen the cork.\n   - Prevent the cork from popping out on its own by holding it firmly and gently easing it out.\n\n5. **Pour and Enjoy**:\n   - Pour the wine into Champagne flutes or white-wine glasses.\n   - Ensure glasses are clean and free from any residues to maintain the wine’s sparkle.\n\nThis protocol emphasizes gentle handling and proper technique to both preserve the quality of the wine and ensure a festive, hazard-free opening."
