ement, indicating that problems persist irrespective of the type or nature of the fermented products.\n   - **Hostility and intimidation**: There is a narrative of hostility from some enforcement officers, including threats and misinformation, which complicates business operations for small producers.\n   - **Persistent misunderstanding about product types**: There appears to be a disconnect or lack of understanding from some regulatory bodies concerning the specifics of live-fermented foods, leading to unnecessary hardships for producers. \n\nThis document highlights the struggles of small businesses, especially those dealing with innovative or less widely understood products like fermented foods, against a backdrop of regulatory and enforcement challenges."
